        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 10. Cigclisula porosa (Canu & Bassler, 1930). A–F, USNM 8514, holotype, Galápagos Islands. A, part of encrusting colony. B, group of zooids. C, primary orifice. D, unusually narrow primary orifice. E, F, ovicelled zooids and elliptical frontal avicularia. Scale bars: A = 500 µm; B = 200 µm; C, D = 100 µm; E, F = 200 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4930679/files/figure.png" .

